S6.T1.caption: Table 1: Test Accuracy (%percent\%) For DP-SCAFFOLD on Synthetic Data, With ϵ=3italic-ϵ3\epsilon=3, l=0.05𝑙0.05l=0.05, s=0.2𝑠0.2s=0.2, (α,β)=(5,5)𝛼𝛽55(\alpha,\beta)=(5,5).
references: Trade-offs between parameters. In DP-SCAFFOLD, a fixed guarantee ϵitalic-ϵ\epsilon can be achieved by different combinations of values for K𝐾K, T𝑇T and σgsubscript𝜎𝑔\sigma_{g}, as shown in Theorem 4.2). We propose to empirically observe these trade-offs on synthetic data under a high privacy regime (ϵ=3)italic-ϵ3(\epsilon=3). The sampling parameters are fixed to l=0.05,s=0.2formulae-sequence𝑙0.05𝑠0.2l=0.05,s=0.2. Given σgsubscript𝜎𝑔\sigma_{g} and K𝐾K, we calculate the maximal value of T𝑇T such that the privacy bound is still maintained after T𝑇T communication rounds. Table 1 shows the test accuracy obtained after these iterations for a high heterogeneity setting (α,β)=(5,5)𝛼𝛽55(\alpha,\beta)=(5,5).

In Section 5 of the main text, we presented these trade-offs for DP-SCAFFOLD under a high level of heterogeneity (see Table 1). We provide below the results of these trade-offs for DP-SCAFFOLD with a lower level of heterogeneity (α,β)=(0,0)𝛼𝛽00(\alpha,\beta)=(0,0) (see Table 4).
We consider again synthetic data with ϵ=3italic-ϵ3\epsilon=3 towards any third party.
To report the test accuracy which is obtained at the end of the iterations, we proceed in two steps: (i) we compute the average test accuracy over the last 10% of the iterations for each random run, (ii) we calculate the mean and the standard deviation over the 3 runs and report them in the tables. We highlight in bold for each row (i.e., for each value of σgsubscript𝜎𝑔\sigma_{g}) in Tables 1,4 the best accuracy score obtained over all values of K𝐾K.

We observe the same trends as the ones described for Table 1 in the main text. Indeed, our results clearly show a trade-off between T𝑇T and K𝐾K for DP-SCAFFOLD under a fixed privacy budget. If K𝐾K is set too low or too large, the performance of the algorithm is sub-optimal either because T𝑇T has to be chosen too low or because control variates are inefficient under few local updates.
